[Frontend Form / Postman]
{
  "email": "ayush@gmail.com",
  "password": "1234",
  "firstName": "Ayush",
  "lastName": "Oriya",
  "keycloakId": "some-id"
}
        |
        |  HTTP POST /api/users/register
        v
[Spring DispatcherServlet]
- Intercepts all incoming HTTP requests
- Finds matching controller method based on URL & HTTP method
        |
        v
[UserController.register(@RequestBody RegisterRequest request)]
- Spring automatically converts JSON → RegisterRequest object
- request.getEmail(), request.getFirstName() etc. now have values from JSON
        |
        v
[UserService.register(request)]
- Reads data from RegisterRequest
- Creates User entity
        |
        v
[UserRepository.save(user)]
- Saves User entity to PostgreSQL DB
- Returns saved User entity (with ID, timestamps)
        |
        v
[UserService.register returns UserResponse]
- Converts User entity → UserResponse DTO
        |
        v
[UserController returns ResponseEntity<UserResponse>]
- Sends JSON response back to frontend
{
  "id": "123",
  "email": "ayush@gmail.com",
  "firstName": "Ayush",
  "lastName": "Oriya",
  "keycloakId": "some-id"
}
        |
        v
[Frontend receives JSON]
- Shows success message, user profile, or proceeds to login
